{
  "analysis": "The terminal is cluttered with interleaved brute-force output and queued commands. We need stop any running process, then run clean diagnostics for the known-good 2-byte stream `4f 02` and our generated `/app/t1.comp`. This will reveal the decoded token sequence for a valid stream versus our invalid encoder output and help identify the arithmetic coding bug.",
  "plan": "Send Ctrl-C to stop the running brute-force/search. Then run a single compact diagnostic block: create `/tmp/good.bin` with bytes `4f 02`, verify `/app/decomp` output, run `/app/decsim` capturing stderr, and run `/app/decsim` on `/app/t1.comp` with clear separators. Use short durations and avoid queuing many commands.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "C-c\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "printf '\\x4f\\x02' > /tmp/good.bin; echo \"GOOD_BYTES\"; od -An -tx1 -v /tmp/good.bin; echo \"GOOD_DECOMP\"; cat /tmp/good.bin | /app/decomp | od -An -tx1 -v; echo \"GOOD_DECSIM\"; cat /tmp/good.bin | /app/decsim > /tmp/good.out 2>/tmp/good.err; head -20 /tmp/good.err; echo \"GOOD_OUT\"; od -An -tx1 -v /tmp/good.out; echo \"T1_BYTES\"; od -An -tx1 -v /app/t1.comp; echo \"T1_DECSIM\"; cat /app/t1.comp | /app/decsim > /tmp/t1.out 2>/tmp/t1.err; head -20 /tmp/t1.err; echo \"T1_OUT\"; od -An -tx1 -v /tmp/t1.out\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    }
  ]
}
